cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "TruthLens — AI Toxicity & Synthetic Media Detector"
message: "If you use TruthLens in research, journalism, or education, please cite it."
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Tom
    family-names: "(mrtomdev)"
    alias: mrtomdev
repository-code: "https://github.com/mrtomdev/truthlens"
url: "https://mrtomdev.github.io/truthlens/"
abstract: >-
  TruthLens is an open-source, on-device browser extension that detects
  AI-generated text (ChatGPT, GPT-4, Claude, Gemini), deepfake images
  (Midjourney, DALL-E, Stable Diffusion, Leonardo, Ideogram, Flux), and
  cloned voices in real time. It runs entirely in the browser with zero
  telemetry, exposing transparent statistical signals rather than a
  black-box score.
keywords:
  - AI detector
  - deepfake detector
  - ChatGPT detector
  - synthetic media detection
  - voice clone detection
  - browser extension
  - Manifest V3
  - privacy-first
  - disinformation
  - media literacy
license: MIT
version: 1.0.0
date-released: 2026-05-13
